ily:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">When a local authority declines to impose a traffic regulation order that is widely – supported by the public, there should be a right of appeal, either to an independent inspector or a magistrate.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We also expressly support the formal submissions made by The Green Lanes Environmental Action Group (GLEAG), by The Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG), by The Peak District Green Lanes Alliance (PDGLA) and our own Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance (YDGLA).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We trust these proposals will be considered.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">4 September</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>